text: Lieke van Wijk (born 18 September 1993) is a Dutch field hockey player. Playing for Netherlands junior teams for 4 years, van Wijk won 4 gold medals; two EuroHockey Junior Nations Championships, one Youth Olympic Games and one Junior World Cup. Lieke van Wijk also plays at an international level for the Netherlands Indoor hockey team. With the team, she won gold at the 2016 EuroHockey Indoor Championship and silver at the 2018 Indoor Hockey World Cup. ==References== ==External Links== Category:1993 births Category:Living people Category:Dutch female field hockey players Category:Field hockey players at the 2010 Summer Youth Olympics Category:Youth Olympic gold medalists for the Netherlands
